<P><H1 align=center>OTHER INCOME DETAILS – DC195</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red><STRONG>NOTE: </STRONG>fields shown in 
red are mandatory and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>This screen is used to gather and store information about other types of 
income (I.e. unearned income) that may be considered when assessing the 
application</P>
<P><H3>Add: </H3>if the applicant has any other type of 
income, click on ‘Add’. This leads to Add / Edit Other Income (DC196)
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on OK leads back to DC195, and any 
details entered will be shown in the box at the top of the screen. The amount 
will also be shown in the ‘Other income’ field
<P></P>
<P><H3>Edit / Delete: </H3>to edit or delete a record, 
highlight the relevant line and click on the appropriate button
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>clicking on ‘OK’ leads to the next screen.
